bug.short_desc: namespace branch: qx.ui.table throws exception on scrolling with mouse wheel when no vertical scrollbar is displayed

long_desc.thetext:
if a qx.ui.table has not vertical scrollbar and the mouse is pointed into the content, trying to scroll leads to a javascript throw exception:
006235: Modification of property "firstVisibleRow" failed with exception: this._rowArr out of bounds: 0,8582.924728754262,Tue Mar 21 2006 00:03:10 GMT+0100,true,1,7739.794370878382,Fri Sep 15 2006 21:22:12 GMT+0200,false,2,8881.939414167791,Fri Nov 17 2006 05:30:00
After this error marking and highlighting gets distorted.
Testcase and screen snapshot is attached
Created attachment 6 screen snapshot which shows the bug

Til, would you consider to apply this patch to svn please?
Changed severity to major.

Your patch fixed a symptom and not the problem.
The problem is that the ScrollBar returns a negative value when it is not needed. I fixed the ScrollBar.
